---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article class="about-content">
				<h1>About Me</h1>
				
				<section>
					<h2>Who I Am</h2>
					<p>
						I'm Manu MA (Manuel Martínez-Almeida), an open-source developer from Spain with a passion for
						creating tools that empower developers worldwide. Currently working at Builder.io, I've spent
						over a decade contributing to projects that have collectively helped millions of developers
						build better applications.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>My Journey</h2>
					<p>
						My coding journey started at a young age. At 15, I founded FORZEFIELD Studios and developed
						<strong>Infinity Field</strong>, a dual-stick shooter for iOS that featured innovative multiplayer
						capabilities through Joypad SDK integration. The game was featured by IGN, AppSpy, and other
						major gaming outlets, teaching me early lessons about performance optimization, user experience,
						and shipping products that people love.
					</p>
					<p>
						From those early days developing games with Cocos2d (where I became a top contributor), I
						transitioned into web technologies and open source, where I found my true calling: building
						tools that make other developers' lives easier.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Major Projects</h2>
					
					<div class="project-detail">
						<h3>Gin (2014 - Present)</h3>
						<p>
							Created Gin, a high-performance HTTP web framework for Go that became the most popular
							web framework in the Go ecosystem with over 86,000 stars on GitHub. Gin provides a
							Martini-like API with performance up to 40 times faster, thanks to httprouter. It's now
							used by thousands of companies worldwide to build production APIs and web services.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="project-detail">
						<h3>Qwik (Co-creator)</h3>
						<p>
							Co-created Qwik, a revolutionary framework that delivers instant-loading web applications
							with O(1) loading time regardless of application complexity. Qwik fundamentally rethinks
							how we build web applications by introducing resumability and fine-grained lazy loading
							at the framework level.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="project-detail">
						<h3>Stencil (Co-creator)</h3>
						<p>
							Co-created Stencil, a toolchain for building scalable, enterprise-ready component systems
							on top of TypeScript and Web Component standards. Stencil components compile to highly
							optimized Web Components that work seamlessly across React, Angular, Vue, and other
							frameworks.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="project-detail">
						<h3>Ionic Framework (Core Developer)</h3>
						<p>
							Served as a core developer on Ionic Framework, one of the most popular cross-platform
							UI toolkits with over 52,000 stars. Contributed to building a powerful framework that
							enables developers to create native-quality iOS, Android, and Progressive Web Apps using
							web technologies.
						</p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Contributions & Impact</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<strong>HTML Specification Contributor:</strong> Contributed to the evolution of web
							standards, helping shape the future of the web platform.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>Conference Speaker:</strong> Shared knowledge and insights at various technical
							conferences about web performance, framework architecture, and modern development practices.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>Open Source Advocate:</strong> Maintained and contributed to numerous open-source
							projects, with collective stars exceeding 200,000 across my repositories.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong>Community Builder:</strong> Active in helping developers through GitHub issues,
							discussions, and mentoring.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Current Focus</h2>
					<p>
						Today, I work at <strong>Builder.io</strong>, where I continue to push the boundaries of
						web development. I'm also the founder of <strong>set.health</strong>, a healthcare technology
						startup focused on improving patient care through innovative digital solutions.
					</p>
					<p>
						Beyond my professional work, I maintain a passion for WebGL and shader programming, creating
						interactive visual experiences that explore the artistic side of code. You can see an example
						of this in the electric field simulation shader powering the background of this portfolio.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Technical Expertise</h2>
					<div class="skills-grid">
						<div class="skill-category">
							<h4>Languages</h4>
							<p>Go, TypeScript, JavaScript, GLSL</p>
						</div>
						<div class="skill-category">
							<h4>Frameworks</h4>
							<p>Qwik, Stencil, Ionic, Astro, React</p>
						</div>
						<div class="skill-category">
							<h4>Specialties</h4>
							<p>Web Performance, Framework Architecture, WebGL, Compiler Design</p>
						</div>
						<div class="skill-category">
							<h4>Focus Areas</h4>
							<p>Developer Experience, Open Source, Web Standards</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Let's Connect</h2>
					<p>
						I'm always interested in connecting with fellow developers, discussing new ideas, or
						exploring collaboration opportunities. Feel free to reach out through:
					</p>
					<ul class="contact-links">
						<li>
							<a href="https://github.com/manucorporat" target="_blank">GitHub</a> - Check out my projects
							and contributions
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/manu-mart%C3%ADnez-almeida-5b390539/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>
							- Professional networking
						</li>
						<li>
							<a href="https://twitter.com/manucorporat" target="_blank">Twitter</a> - Thoughts on tech
							and development
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-content {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	h1 {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: 3em;
	}

	h2 {
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
		padding-bottom: 0.3em;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}

	h3 {
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		margin-top: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}

	h4 {
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}

	.project-detail {
		margin-bottom: 2em;
		padding-left: 1em;
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
	}

	.project-detail h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	ul {
		line-height: 1.9;
	}

	.skills-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5em;
		margin-top: 1.5em;
	}

	.skill-category {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8f9ff 0%, #ffffff 100%);
		padding: 1.5em;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 2px solid #e0e0ff;
	}

	.skill-category h4 {
		margin-top: 0;
		margin-bottom: 0.8em;
	}

	.skill-category p {
		margin: 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.contact-links {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}

	.contact-links li {
		margin-bottom: 0.8em;
	}

	.contact-links a {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.contact-links a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.skills-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
